{"id":"mini-test-29-demonstrative-pronouns","title":"Mini Test 29: Demonstrative Pronouns","description":"Practice dieser, jener, welcher, solcher in all cases","duration":18,"category":"grammar","focus":"Pronouns","questions":[{"id":"q1","type":"multiple-choice","text":"___ Mann dort ist mein Lehrer.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Dieser"},{"id":"b","text":"Dieses"},{"id":"c","text":"Diese"},{"id":"d","text":"Diesen"}],"correctAnswerId":"a","explanation":"Nominativ maskulin: dieser Mann","explanationDetail":"Dieser/diese/dieses decline like der/die/das. Masculine nominative: dieser.","tags":["pronouns","demonstrative"]},{"id":"q2","type":"multiple-choice","text":"___ Buch habe ich gelesen.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Dieser"},{"id":"b","text":"Dieses"},{"id":"c","text":"Diesen"},{"id":"d","text":"Diesem"}],"correctAnswerId":"b","explanation":"Akkusativ neuter: dieses Buch","explanationDetail":"Das Buch (neuter) → dieses Buch. Akkusativ neuter = nominative.","tags":["pronouns","demonstrative"]},{"id":"q3","type":"multiple-choice","text":"Mit ___ Frau habe ich gesprochen.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"diese"},{"id":"b","text":"dieser"},{"id":"c","text":"dieses"},{"id":"d","text":"diesen"}],"correctAnswerId":"b","explanation":"Dativ feminin: mit dieser Frau","explanationDetail":"Mit + Dativ. Die Frau → dieser Frau (Dativ feminine).","tags":["pronouns","demonstrative"]},{"id":"q4","type":"multiple-choice","text":"___ Kinder spielen im Garten.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Dieser"},{"id":"b","text":"Diese"},{"id":"c","text":"Dieses"},{"id":"d","text":"Diesen"}],"correctAnswerId":"b","explanation":"Nominativ/Akkusativ plural: diese Kinder","explanationDetail":"Plural: diese (same for nominative and accusative).","tags":["pronouns","demonstrative"]},{"id":"q5","type":"multiple-choice","text":"Ich kenne ___ Mann nicht.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"dieser"},{"id":"b","text":"diesen"},{"id":"c","text":"diesem"},{"id":"d","text":"dieses"}],"correctAnswerId":"b","explanation":"Akkusativ maskulin: diesen Mann","explanationDetail":"Kennen takes accusative. Der Mann → diesen Mann.","tags":["pronouns","demonstrative"]},{"id":"q6","type":"multiple-choice","text":"Welche Bluse? ___ hier.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Jener"},{"id":"b","text":"Jene"},{"id":"c","text":"Jenes"},{"id":"d","text":"Jenen"}],"correctAnswerId":"b","explanation":"Jene = that one (feminine), here pointing to Bluse","explanationDetail":"Jener/jene/jenes = that one (further away). Feminine: jene.","tags":["pronouns","demonstrative"]},{"id":"q7","type":"multiple-choice","text":"___ Tag werde ich nicht vergessen.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Jener"},{"id":"b","text":"Jenen"},{"id":"c","text":"Jenes"},{"id":"d","text":"Jener"}],"correctAnswerId":"b","explanation":"Akkusativ maskulin: jenen Tag","explanationDetail":"Vergessen + Akkusativ. Der Tag → jenen Tag.","tags":["pronouns","demonstrative"]},{"id":"q8","type":"multiple-choice","text":"Mit ___ Ergebnis sind wir zufrieden.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"dieser"},{"id":"b","text":"diesem"},{"id":"c","text":"diesen"},{"id":"d","text":"dieses"}],"correctAnswerId":"b","explanation":"Dativ neuter: mit diesem Ergebnis","explanationDetail":"Mit + Dativ. Das Ergebnis → diesem Ergebnis.","tags":["pronouns","demonstrative"]},{"id":"q9","type":"multiple-choice","text":"___ Film war langweilig.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Jener"},{"id":"b","text":"Jene"},{"id":"c","text":"Jenes"},{"id":"d","text":"Jenen"}],"correctAnswerId":"a","explanation":"Nominativ maskulin: jener Film","explanationDetail":"Jener declines like der. Masculine nominative: jener.","tags":["pronouns","demonstrative"]},{"id":"q10","type":"multiple-choice","text":"Welcher Hut? ___ auf dem Tisch.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Welcher"},{"id":"b","text":"Welchen"},{"id":"c","text":"Welches"},{"id":"d","text":"Welchem"}],"correctAnswerId":"a","explanation":"Welcher as demonstrative: der auf dem Tisch (nominative)","explanationDetail":"Welcher can mean 'which one'. Here: der (one) on the table = welcher.","tags":["pronouns","demonstrative"]},{"id":"q11","type":"multiple-choice","text":"Solche ___ passieren oft.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Sache"},{"id":"b","text":"Sachen"},{"id":"c","text":"Sache"},{"id":"d","text":"Sach"}],"correctAnswerId":"b","explanation":"Solche + plural: solche Sachen","explanationDetail":"Solcher/solche/solches = such. With plural noun: solche Sachen.","tags":["pronouns","demonstrative"]},{"id":"q12","type":"multiple-choice","text":"Ich habe ___ Brief noch nicht geöffnet.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"diesen"},{"id":"b","text":"dieser"},{"id":"c","text":"diesem"},{"id":"d","text":"dieses"}],"correctAnswerId":"a","explanation":"Akkusativ maskulin: diesen Brief","explanationDetail":"Haben + object in accusative. Der Brief → diesen Brief.","tags":["pronouns","demonstrative"]},{"id":"q13","type":"multiple-choice","text":"Nach ___ Stunde können wir gehen.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"diese"},{"id":"b","text":"dieser"},{"id":"c","text":"dieses"},{"id":"d","text":"diesen"}],"correctAnswerId":"b","explanation":"Dativ feminin: nach dieser Stunde","explanationDetail":"Nach + Dativ. Die Stunde → dieser Stunde.","tags":["pronouns","demonstrative"]},{"id":"q14","type":"multiple-choice","text":"___ Problem ist schwer.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Dieser"},{"id":"b","text":"Diese"},{"id":"c","text":"Dieses"},{"id":"d","text":"Diesen"}],"correctAnswerId":"c","explanation":"Nominativ neuter: dieses Problem","explanationDetail":"Das Problem (neuter) → dieses Problem.","tags":["pronouns","demonstrative"]},{"id":"q15","type":"multiple-choice","text":"Er erinnert sich an ___ Zeit.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"diese"},{"id":"b","text":"dieser"},{"id":"c","text":"diesen"},{"id":"d","text":"diesem"}],"correctAnswerId":"a","explanation":"Akkusativ feminin: an diese Zeit","explanationDetail":"An + Akkusativ (motion/relation). Die Zeit → diese Zeit.","tags":["pronouns","demonstrative"]},{"id":"q16","type":"multiple-choice","text":"Von ___ Idee halte ich nichts.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"diese"},{"id":"b","text":"dieser"},{"id":"c","text":"dieses"},{"id":"d","text":"diesen"}],"correctAnswerId":"b","explanation":"Dativ feminin: von dieser Idee","explanationDetail":"Von + Dativ. Die Idee → dieser Idee.","tags":["pronouns","demonstrative"]},{"id":"q17","type":"multiple-choice","text":"___ Äpfel sind frisch.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Jener"},{"id":"b","text":"Jene"},{"id":"c","text":"Jenes"},{"id":"d","text":"Jenen"}],"correctAnswerId":"b","explanation":"Nominativ plural: jene Äpfel","explanationDetail":"Plural: jene (like diese). Jene Äpfel = those apples.","tags":["pronouns","demonstrative"]},{"id":"q18","type":"multiple-choice","text":"Wir brauchen ___ Hilfe.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"diese"},{"id":"b","text":"dieser"},{"id":"c","text":"dieses"},{"id":"d","text":"diesen"}],"correctAnswerId":"a","explanation":"Akkusativ feminin: diese Hilfe","explanationDetail":"Brauchen + Akkusativ. Die Hilfe → diese Hilfe.","tags":["pronouns","demonstrative"]},{"id":"q19","type":"multiple-choice","text":"Bei ___ Wetter bleiben wir zu Hause.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"diese"},{"id":"b","text":"dieser"},{"id":"c","text":"diesem"},{"id":"d","text":"diesen"}],"correctAnswerId":"c","explanation":"Dativ neuter: bei diesem Wetter","explanationDetail":"Bei + Dativ. Das Wetter → diesem Wetter.","tags":["pronouns","demonstrative"]},{"id":"q20","type":"multiple-choice","text":"___ Stuhl ist kaputt.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Jener"},{"id":"b","text":"Jenen"},{"id":"c","text":"Jenes"},{"id":"d","text":"Jener"}],"correctAnswerId":"a","explanation":"Nominativ maskulin: jener Stuhl","explanationDetail":"Der Stuhl → jener Stuhl (that chair over there).","tags":["pronouns","demonstrative"]},{"id":"q21","type":"multiple-choice","text":"Mit ___ Leuten arbeite ich gern.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"diese"},{"id":"b","text":"diesen"},{"id":"c","text":"dieser"},{"id":"d","text":"dieses"}],"correctAnswerId":"b","explanation":"Dativ plural: mit diesen Leuten","explanationDetail":"Mit + Dativ. Die Leute (plural) → diesen Leuten.","tags":["pronouns","demonstrative"]},{"id":"q22","type":"multiple-choice","text":"___ Wetter ist selten. (Solcher/solche/solches)","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Solcher"},{"id":"b","text":"Solche"},{"id":"c","text":"Solches"},{"id":"d","text":"Solchen"}],"correctAnswerId":"c","explanation":"Neuter: solches Wetter","explanationDetail":"Solcher/solche/solches = such. Das Wetter (neuter) → solches Wetter.","tags":["pronouns","demonstrative"]},{"id":"q23","type":"multiple-choice","text":"Ich gebe ___ Kind ein Bonbon.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"dieser"},{"id":"b","text":"dieses"},{"id":"c","text":"diesem"},{"id":"d","text":"diesen"}],"correctAnswerId":"c","explanation":"Dativ neuter: diesem Kind","explanationDetail":"Geben + Dativ (person). Das Kind → diesem Kind.","tags":["pronouns","demonstrative"]},{"id":"q24","type":"multiple-choice","text":"___ Frau kenne ich nicht.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Jener"},{"id":"b","text":"Jene"},{"id":"c","text":"Jenen"},{"id":"d","text":"Jener"}],"correctAnswerId":"b","explanation":"Akkusativ feminin: jene Frau (same as nominative for feminine)","explanationDetail":"Jene Frau – feminine accusative = jene (same form as nominative).","tags":["pronouns","demonstrative"]},{"id":"q25","type":"multiple-choice","text":"Über ___ Thema haben wir gesprochen.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"diese"},{"id":"b","text":"dieses"},{"id":"c","text":"diesem"},{"id":"d","text":"diesen"}],"correctAnswerId":"b","explanation":"Akkusativ neuter: über dieses Thema","explanationDetail":"Sprechen über + Akkusativ. Das Thema → dieses Thema.","tags":["pronouns","demonstrative"]},{"id":"q26","type":"multiple-choice","text":"Welches Auto? ___ dort drüben.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Dieser"},{"id":"b","text":"Dieses"},{"id":"c","text":"Jener"},{"id":"d","text":"Jenes"}],"correctAnswerId":"d","explanation":"Jenes = that one (neuter), for something further away","explanationDetail":"Dort drüben = over there. Jenes (that one there) fits.","tags":["pronouns","demonstrative"]},{"id":"q27","type":"multiple-choice","text":"Er hat ___ Fehler gemacht.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"dieser"},{"id":"b","text":"diesen"},{"id":"c","text":"diesem"},{"id":"d","text":"dieses"}],"correctAnswerId":"b","explanation":"Akkusativ maskulin: diesen Fehler","explanationDetail":"Machen + Akkusativ. Der Fehler → diesen Fehler.","tags":["pronouns","demonstrative"]},{"id":"q28","type":"multiple-choice","text":"Für ___ Arbeit bekommt sie wenig Geld.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"diese"},{"id":"b","text":"dieser"},{"id":"c","text":"dieses"},{"id":"d","text":"diesen"}],"correctAnswerId":"a","explanation":"Akkusativ feminin: für diese Arbeit","explanationDetail":"Für + Akkusativ. Die Arbeit → diese Arbeit.","tags":["pronouns","demonstrative"]},{"id":"q29","type":"multiple-choice","text":"___ Geschichten sind interessant.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Dieser"},{"id":"b","text":"Diese"},{"id":"c","text":"Dieses"},{"id":"d","text":"Diesen"}],"correctAnswerId":"b","explanation":"Nominativ plural: diese Geschichten","explanationDetail":"Plural nominative: diese. Diese Geschichten sind interessant.","tags":["pronouns","demonstrative"]},{"id":"q30","type":"multiple-choice","text":"Ich warte auf ___ Zug.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"diese"},{"id":"b","text":"dieser"},{"id":"c","text":"diesen"},{"id":"d","text":"diesem"}],"correctAnswerId":"c","explanation":"Akkusativ maskulin: auf diesen Zug","explanationDetail":"Warten auf + Akkusativ. Der Zug → diesen Zug.","tags":["pronouns","demonstrative"]}]}
